  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Slice your<strong> chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced chestnut mushrooms </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until lightly golden and slightly softened, then transfer to a plate, reserving the pan</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681899142211-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681899142211-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681899142211-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681899142211-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681899142211-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the mushrooms are cooking, chop your<strong> waxy potatoes </strong>into quarters</p><p>Add the chopped potatoes to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the lower part of the oven for 20-25 minutes or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>roasted potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681899149510-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681899149510-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681899149510-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681899149510-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681899149510-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> leek[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leeks </strong>and cook for 5-6 min<strong> </strong>or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681899229967-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681899229967-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681899229967-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681899229967-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681899229967-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and cut your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> into 3 wedges per person</p><p>Once the leeks have softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with 1 <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span> knob[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>of <strong>butter </strong>and 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Remove the pan from the heat and add your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>cider vinegar</strong> (you’ll use the rest later!), a splash of <strong>cold water</strong>, a<strong> </strong>pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and stir it all together – these are your <strong>creamy leeks</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
